║   HAWKES MODEL WITH POVERTY RATE COVARIATE                   ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

SPECIFICATION:
  Background: μ(d,y) = exp(β₀ + γ·log(pop) + δ·poverty_rate + Σ β_year)
  Triggering: α(marks) = exp(β₀_trig + β_violence·violent + β_state·intervention)
  Kernel: g(t) = exp(-β·t)
  Intensity: λ(t) = μ(d,y) + Σ α(marks_i)·g(t-t_i)

HYPOTHESIS:
  → Larger districts have lower poverty (cor = -0.480)
  → If poverty explains sub-proportional effect, γ should increase
  → Baseline γ ≈ 0.35, with poverty expect γ ≈ 0.6-1.0

